#!/usr/bin/env bash
# shellcheck disable=SC2034
#
# pdrx - Portable Dynamic Reproducible gnu/linuX
# Pure Bash tool for fully reproducible Linux system setups.
# Imperative install/remove with automatic declarative config sync.
# Supports: apt, dnf, yum, pacman, zypper, brew, flatpak, snap, cargo, winget
#
# Scope (deliberately bounded — see README "Scope" section):
#   IN:  packages, repo/PPA sources, dotfiles, DE settings, enabled systemd units
#   OUT: partitioning, fstab, LUKS, filesystem provisioning — that's cloud-init /
#        Ansible / Nix territory. pdrx declares what's installed and enabled on
#        top of an already-provisioned OS, not the OS itself.
#
# No Nix dependency. Works on Debian, Ubuntu, Fedora, Arch, openSUSE, Windows (winget), etc.

